# Website Deploy After Push

When you push commits to GitHub that change `website/` in **urp-ct-mcp-studio**, schedule an async deploy to **https://ct-mcp.suherman.net/** (Cloud Run `ct-mcp-website`).

Hooks call `scripts/deploy-trigger.cjs` → `scripts/deploy-runner.cjs` (same tracked pipeline as `npm run ci`).

## When this applies

- Files under `website/` changed in commits being pushed
- Push target is GitHub (`origin` or equivalent)
- GCP deploy is configured (`npm run login`, valid ADC)

## Required workflow after a successful push

1. Push first (per `git-push-after-commit.mdc`):
   ```bash
   git push
   ```
2. Hooks schedule deploy automatically (`githooks/pre-push`, `githooks/post-commit`). If hooks are disabled, trigger manually:
   ```bash
   node scripts/deploy-trigger.cjs --repo ct-mcp-website
   ```
3. Tell the user deploy started in the background and how to monitor:
   ```bash
   npm run ci
   ```
   Do not block on `npm run deploy:website` unless the user asks to wait.

## Monitor local deploy pipeline

```bash
npm run ci                  # live dashboard (Ctrl+C safe)
npm run ci -- --once        # snapshot
npm run deploy:retry        # retry failed/pending
npm run deploy:stop -- --repo ct-mcp-website
```

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `logs/deployments.json` | Deploy state |
| `logs/ct-mcp-website/*.log` | Per-deploy output |
| `.git/post-push-website.log` | Push hook worker |
| `.git/post-commit-website.log` | Commit hook worker |

## Disable

```bash
CT_MCP_POST_PUSH_WEBSITE=0 git push
CT_MCP_POST_COMMIT_WEBSITE=0 git commit ...
```

## Do not

- Run `deploy:website` synchronously in chat unless the user explicitly asks to wait for deploy completion
- Deploy when push failed or was rejected
- Force-push to `main`/`master` to trigger deploy

See also: `scripts/ci-deploy-status.cjs`, `scripts/deploy-runner.cjs`, `npm run deploy:website`.
